article.headline: Long Beach State 61, Montana 53
article.story:
LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Petra Glaser and Crystal McCutcheon
scored 13 points each in leading Long Beach State to a 61-53
nonconference victory over Montana Wednesday night in the 49ers'
opening game.

McCutcheon went 6-for-6 from the line near the end to secure the
victory.

Junior Katie Edward scored 15 points in leading the Lady Griz.
Senior Hollie Tyler had 10 points and 10 rebounds.

Montana of the Big Sky Conference (1-1) held a 45-42 rebounding
advantage and held Long Beach to under 37 percent shooting, but the
Lady Griz could only hit on 29.7 percent of their shots.
